cause he played fully offensively and non-defensively (see Aragorn's hit'n'run evading speedbuff syndrome) but the complaints from many light tanks are that full-offensive should be a viable spec, while many people find that you gain nothing form being 50/50/28 that you don't get from being 44/44/44 and RR6, with DReflex 1...<br>
<br>
My point has been that Boromir should be respected among the offensive tanks because of his whole-hearted attampt to be as offensive as possible, and kill ALL the enemies near him (even the ones that werent' a threat... like Skalds in a way...).<br>
<br>
I also think he was a much more likeable character than he could have been portrayed, and wasn't at all L33t1st  as me might have been, admitting when things went wrong because of him, and noticeably thinking highly of the lowbies in the group.<br>
<br>
We could use more daoc players like this guy, in other words.<br>
<br>
The argument against this is simply that he was non team-spirited when he tried to take the Ring, but surely stubbornness is a virtue - seeing as without it, the light tank would soon be fairly non-existent.<br>
<br>
